  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cafe Staff",
  "description": "<p>We're looking for fun-loving idividuals to join our small team! We're a dessert/snacks cafe that is adjacent to to a kids gym. You will be working in a family-centric environment to provide the best service to our customers and members.</p><p><u>Requirements:</u></p><p>- Open and fun individual who likes kids</p><p>- F&B experience not needed but coffee making skills are a plus</p><p>- Friendly</p><p>- Punctual and responsible</p><p>- Able to work weekends and shift timings<br /></p><p><u>Job responsibilities:</u></p><p>ou will be required to prepare and serve hot and cold beverages, including various types of coffee, tea, smoothies and milkshakes.</p><p>You will also be serving ice cream and preparing waffles, as well as crepes.</p><p>Responsibilities include educating customers on our drinks menu, making recommendations based on their preferences, up-selling special items and taking orders.</p><p>To be successful in this role, you should have customer service skills and knowledge of how brewing equipment operates.</p><p>You should also be able to work weekends and various shifts.</p><p>Ultimately, you’ll ensure a comfortable and excellent drinking and dining experience for our guests.</p><p>Being affiliated to a kids gym, you should expect a family-centric crowd at our cafe.</p><p></p><p>Responsibilities</p><p>* • Greet customers as they enter</p><p>* • Give customers cafe menus and answer their questions regarding ingredients</p><p>* • Take orders while paying attention to details (e.g. preferences of coffee blend, dairy and sugar ratios)</p><p>* • Prepare beverages following recipes</p><p>* • Prepare snacks/food following recipes</p><p>* • Serve beverages and prepared food, like waffles, crepes, etc.</p><p>* • Receive and process payments (cash and credit cards)</p><p>* • Keep the bar area clean</p><p>* • Maintain stock of clean mugs and plates</p><p>* • Check if brewing equipment operates properly and report any maintenance needs</p><p>* • Comply with health and safety regulations</p><p>* • Communicate customer feedback to managers and recommend new menu items</p><p></p><p>Requirements and skills</p><p>* • Previous work experience as a Barista or Waiter/Waitress</p><p>* • Hands-on experience with brewing equipment/food preparation equipment</p><p>* • Knowledge of sanitation regulations</p><p>* • Flexibility to work weekends and various shifts</p><p>* • Basic math skills</p><p>* • Ability to gauge customers’ preferences</p><p>* • Excellent communication skills</p>",
